                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">Thames police-constable, No.</hi> 11.) On the 12th of April I fell in with the prisoner coming on shore at Bell Wharf-stairs, Shadwell, about two o'clock in the morning—he was carrying a bundle of clothes—I asked where he was going—he said, "On shore"—I said, "For what purpose?"—he said, to run away from his ship—I took him back to the ship, overhauled the things, and found these things—I asked him what ship he belonged to—he said, the <hi rend="italic">Endymion.</hi>
